article.headline: South Alabama 68, New Orleans 61
article.story: MOBILE, Ala. (AP) -- Mario Jointer scored 21 points to lead South Alabama to a 68-61 victory over New Orleans on Thursday night. Jointer shot 5-of-7 from 3-point range and had seven rebounds for South Alabama (8-15, 5-7 Sun Belt Conference). Daniel Northern added 15 points and eight rebounds. South Alabama led 30-26 at halftime and shot 43.8 percent from the field. Bo McCalebb scored a game-high 23 points for New Orleans (11-14, 6-5) and had four assists. Jamie McNeilly added 12 points, and Todd Bostic shot 3-of-8 from 3-point range. The team shot 47.2 percent from the field.
